HEADWORD: Angariation
<hw>An*ga"ri*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>angariatio</ets>, fr. L. <ets>angaria</ets> service to a lord,
villenage, fr. <ets>angarius</ets>, Gr. <grk>'a`ggaros</grk> (a Persian
word), a courier for carrying royal dispatches.]</ety> <def>Exaction of
forced service; compulsion.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
